                     <h3 class="content">April 24, 2005</h3>
                     <a id="a000117"></a>
                     <div class="content" id="entry-117">
                        <h3 class="content">pancake bunny!</h3>
                        <div class="content">
                           <div class="content">
                              <p><img src="http://drzaius.ics.uci.edu/mt3.14/johannab/archives/oolong-pancake.jpg" width="200" height="150"></p>

<p>so, some of you may know how much i love that photo of the bunny with the pancake on his head.  words cannot describe [muhduh!].  well finally, thanks to clive thompson, i now know the origin of these photos.  they are of a <a href="http://www.fsinet.or.jp/~sokaisha/rabbit/rabbit.htm">little japanese bunny named oolong</a> who, very sadly, has hopped off this mortal coil.</p>

<p>[thanks <a href="http://www.collisiondetection.net/mt/archives/2005/04/oolong_was_a_ra.html#001182">collision detection</a>]</p>
                              
